          "id": "medmcqa-30525681-a5ee-4629-b61a-04c0bd76ee77",
          "text": "A patient of 18 years of age presents with sudden agonising pain in the groin and the lower abdomen. The patient feels nausea and gives a history of vomiting. On physical examination, the testis seems high. The cremasteric reflex is lost. What is the most possible cause?",
