          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Hyperophic pyloric stenosis is more common in males. Male : female incidence is 4:1. Peristalsis is seen from left to right across the upper abdomen. Retention vomiting means vomiting due to any mechanical obstruction occurring usually hours after ingestion of a meal. In hyperophic pyloric stenosis the vomiting usually occur 10 to 30 min after the feed. Ref: Nelson 17/e, Page 1229"
