          "explanation": "Ans is a (Prostate cancer) Though increased levels of PSA is seen in Prostate cancer, BPH and Prostatitis; levels above 20 ng/mL would be seen almost only in Prostate cancer. BPH and prostatitis would not cause such a rise in PSA."
