          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'b' i.e., Duodenal ulcer Both esophageal varices and duodenal ulcer are causes of massive upper GI bleed. Although it is difficult to reach a diagnosis by clinical history and physical examination alone, variceal bleed is less likely as there are no stigmata of chronic liver disease or poal hypeension."
